# Identifier Naming & Registries

## Technical vs. display names

- All technical identifiers MUST use lowercase kebab-case ASCII.
- Chinese characters are allowed ONLY in:
  - Documentation files under `docs/`.
  - Page copy and `seo.*` fields inside `content/<locale>/pages/*.json`.
  - `navigation[].label`, `company.displayName`, marketing copy in `site.config.ts`.
  - Registry display-name columns.
- The following MUST NEVER contain Chinese characters: `siteSlug`, theme ID, package names, folder names, Cloudflare Pages Project names, environment variable names, import paths, JSON file names, JSON field names.

## Required registries

Every site and every theme MUST be recorded in a Markdown registry under `docs/registries/`.

### `docs/registries/site-registry.md`

One row per site, including:

- `siteSlug`
- Chinese name (中文公司名称)
- English display name
- Legal entity
- Industry
- Theme (theme ID)
- Domain
- Cloudflare Pages Project name
- Status (e.g. `active`, `staging`, `archived`)
- Purpose (one sentence)

### `docs/registries/theme-registry.md`

One row per theme, including:

- Theme ID
- Chinese name (中文主题名称)
- Package directory (`packages/theme-<id>`)
- CSS root class (`.theme-<id>`)
- CSS prefix (e.g. `.ims-*`)
- Scenario / target industries
- Visual keywords
- Status (e.g. `active`, `draft`, `archived`)
- Theme document path (`docs/themes/<id>.md`)

The registries are the single source of truth for "what sites exist" and "what themes exist". Any creation, deletion, or status change MUST update them.
